Vespula rufa
(Linnaeus, 1758)

– Hind tibia with short yellow and long black hairs on outer margins (
Fig. 35
). Anterior angles of clypeus sharply produced in queens (
Fig. 36
). Parasitic species, without workers. Males: Apex of aedeagus straight in middle, sides of its apical part distinctly emarginated (
Fig. 37
). ......................................................... 

